import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='population', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="population", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Population')
    ax.axhline(y=data['population'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Population: {:.2f}'.format(data['population'].mean()))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    return plt;

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('state')['engineers'].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='engineers', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="engineers", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Number of Engineers')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of engineers across the states?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('Year').sum().reset_index()
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Hurricanes', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of hurricanes across the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
